      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to knock the form of ROAM (4) who has put together four wins and a second from her last five starts. Came from a wider barrier than this to land a hat trick at Maryborough last time out, scoring by close to 8 metres. Can continue the strong form. WICKED WIZARD (1) continued his consistent form and took his strike rate at this circuit and distance to 50 per cent when winning from wider last week. Up in grade but gets the ace draw. ULTIMATE EMPIRE (10) scored two starts back at Menangle then gave nothing else a chance last start, coming from this barrier to cruise home by 17 metres at Penrith. A repeat of that performance would see him tough to stop. DEMBE (7) is hard to overlook after scoring first-up last start by 1.2 metres at Shepparton. Draws wider but won his only previous second-up attempt and has upside.",
